Portions of this software adapt or synthesize methodology from:

- jamditis/claude-skills-journalism (MIT License) — by Jay Amditis. Used in
  the web-archiving, content-access, and social-media-intelligence skills.
- Bellingcat training materials (https://bellingcat.com/) — investigation
  techniques referenced in the investigate skill.
- GIJN methodology publications (https://gijn.org/) — Miranda Patrucic &
  Jelena Cosic, "Introduction to Investigative Journalism: Following the
  Money," November 2024, CC BY-ND 4.0.
- Jim Shultz, "Follow the Money: A Guide to Monitoring Budgets and Oil and
  Gas Revenues," Revenue Watch / Open Society Institute, 2005.
- Derek Bowler, "Tracing Beneficial Ownership with OSINT for Financial
  Crime," EBU Eurovision News Spotlight, December 2025.

See individual skill files for attribution headers.
